==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Point man
<hw>Point" man`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>-men</plw> <pr>(-m<it>e</it>n)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>the lead soldier in a foot patrol under combat conditions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a person who takes a conspicuous public position in proposing a new idea or initiating a new policy, who may become a target of criticism for those opposed.</def>  ⟦ldquo⟧The Secretary of State served as <ex>point man</ex> for the administration's new China policy.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pointrel</ent>⟦br⟧
